const faqs = [
  {
    q: "My convection oven won't ignite. What's wrong?",
    a: "Most common cause on gas convection ovens: igniter failure (year 5 to 8 typical). On Vulcan VC4 and VC6, the spark igniter electrode pits and stops sparking reliably. Replacement runs $180 to $320. Less common: failed gas valve coil, flame sensor coated with combustion residue, thermocouple weak. We diagnose with multimeter test on the igniter, gas pressure check, and visual inspection of the burner assembly.",
  },
  {
    q: "Do you service Blodgett Mark V and ZEPHAIRE convection ovens?",
    a: "Yes. Blodgett Mark V is one of the most common LA bakery and restaurant convection ovens. Common service: convection fan motor (year 6 to 9), drive belt wear (Mark V uses belt-driven fan, replacement $180 to $280), thermostat, door gasket. ZEPHAIRE service tree is similar with stronger door hinge components. See <a href=\"/brands/blodgett-oven-repair/\">Blodgett oven repair brand page</a>.",
  },
  {
    q: "How long does a commercial convection oven last?",
    a: "12 to 18 years with proper maintenance. Heavy-use bakery ovens skew toward 12, lower-volume restaurant ovens to 18+. The convection fan motor is usually the limiting component (year 6 to 10 typical wear). Brass burner ovens (Vulcan VC, Southbend Marathoner Gold) outlast cast iron alternatives. Door gasket is a routine replace at year 4 to 7 across all brands.",
  },
  {
    q: "My convection oven heats unevenly. What's wrong?",
    a: "Most likely the convection fan is not circulating air effectively. Possibilities: fan motor speed reduced from worn bearings (motor still runs but at lower RPM), drive belt slipping or stretched (Blodgett Mark V especially), or fan blade itself loose on the shaft. Also check door gasket compression, a leaky door drops oven temperature on the door side. We diagnose with infrared thermometer at multiple rack positions and fan RPM measurement.",
  },
  {
    q: "Do you do annual maintenance contracts on convection ovens?",
    a: "Yes. Annual contracts include door gasket inspection, fan motor amperage measurement, igniter and burner inspection (gas), thermostat calibration, drive belt tension check (where applicable). Contract pricing reduces per-visit cost vs reactive scheduling. Bakery and high-volume restaurant operations especially benefit from annual contracts because the failure modes are predictable.",
  },
  {
    q: "Vulcan vs Blodgett vs Southbend, which is more reliable?",
    a: "Honest answer. Vulcan VC4 and VC6 (ITW Food Equipment Group) have the broadest LA install base and the most accessible parts pipeline through ITW distribution. Blodgett Mark V (Middleby) is the bakery favorite for even bake but has the belt-drive fan that adds a routine wear item. Southbend Marathoner Gold (Middleby) sits between, slightly less common in LA. All three are repairable through year 15+ with parts availability. We don't push customers toward any specific brand, we work with what you have.",
  },
  {
    q: "What's your warranty?",
    a: "90 days SDAR labor warranty on every repair. Component manufacturer warranties (Vulcan, Blodgett, Southbend, Garland) processed separately through the manufacturer's authorized network. BHGS Licensed #A49573. EPA 608 Universal certified (#1346255700410). BBB A+ accredited.",
  },
];

