<CommercialHero
  title="Commercial Convection Oven Repair Los Angeles"
  subtitle="Blodgett Mark V, Vulcan VC4/VC6, Southbend Marathoner Gold across LA, OC, Ventura. $120 commercial diagnostic. BHGS Licensed #A49573."
  heroImageTitle="Commercial Convection Oven Repair"
/>

<!-- 01 INTRO -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">01 · Convection oven service</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Convection ovens are the workhorse of LA commercial kitchens. Predictable failure modes, accessible parts.</h2>

    <p>Commercial convection ovens (Blodgett Mark V and ZEPHAIRE, Vulcan VC4 and VC6, Southbend Marathoner Gold, Garland Master Series, Bakers Pride Cyclone) are the dominant convection equipment in LA, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, and Riverside restaurant and bakery kitchens. Mid-tier commercial price ($3,000 to $12,000 new). Most common type. Most accessible parts pipeline.</p>

    <p>The failure modes are predictable. Convection fan motor at year 6 to 9. Drive belt wear (Blodgett Mark V specifically, belt-driven fan adds a routine wear item). Igniter on gas models at year 5 to 8. Door gasket compression at year 4 to 7. Thermostat drift over time. None of these are catastrophic. All are repairable through year 15 to 18 of service life with annual maintenance.</p>

    <p>We service convection ovens across all five SoCal counties. <strong>$120 commercial diagnostic, waived with repair.</strong> BHGS Licensed #A49573. EPA 608 Universal certified (#1346255700410). BBB A+ accredited.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 02 COMMON FAILURES -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">02 · Common convection oven failures</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">What we diagnose most often.</h2>

    <ol class="failure-list">
      <li><strong>Convection fan motor (year 6 to 9).</strong> Most common service item. Bearings worn, motor speed reduced. Air doesn't circulate well, oven heats unevenly. $480 to $720 replacement.</li>
      <li><strong>Drive belt wear (Blodgett Mark V specifically).</strong> Belt stretches or slips. Fan still runs but at lower RPM. Replace belt and check tensioner. $180 to $280 with labor.</li>
      <li><strong>Door gasket compression.</strong> Door seal leaks, oven temp drops on door side, longer cook times. Year 4 to 7 typical replacement. $260 to $420 per gasket.</li>
      <li><strong>Igniter (gas models).</strong> Spark igniter electrode pits or hot-surface igniter element burns out. Vulcan VC and Southbend Marathoner Gold spark systems most common. $180 to $320 replacement.</li>
      <li><strong>Thermostat or temperature controller.</strong> Temperature reading drifts, oven runs hot or cold relative to setpoint. $260 to $420 replacement plus calibration.</li>
      <li><strong>Door switch / interlock.</strong> Safety shutoff that disables burners when door opens. Switch contacts wear, oven won't fire. $180 to $280 replacement.</li>
      <li><strong>Heating element (electric models).</strong> Element open-circuits at year 8 to 12. Standard wear. $480 to $780 replacement.</li>
      <li><strong>Light bulbs (interior).</strong> Routine replacement, $40 to $80 per fixture.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 03 REAL REPAIR STORIES -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">03 · Recent convection oven repairs</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Composite stories from the route.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Four convection oven jobs from the past 90 days. Names omitted; the technical scenarios are typical of what we see weekly.</p>

    <div class="story-grid">
      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Bakery in Glendale · Blodgett Mark V, 8 years old</h3>
        <p>Uneven bake, top rack cooking faster than bottom. Diagnosed: convection fan bearings worn (reduced RPM) plus drive belt stretched. Replaced fan motor and drive belt as a paired set (always replace together on Mark V, mismatched belt and motor fails again within months). Total: $120 + $580 motor + $120 belt + $30 supplies = $850.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Restaurant in Studio City · Vulcan VC6, 6 years old</h3>
        <p>Won't ignite reliably. Diagnosed: spark igniter electrode pitted plus thermostat drift (reading 25°F low). Replaced igniter and thermostat, recalibrated. Total: $120 + $280 igniter + $260 thermostat = $560 (labor included in part pricing on this size job).</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Catering kitchen in West Hollywood · Southbend Marathoner Gold, 9 years old</h3>
        <p>Oven won't fire when door is closed normally but will fire if door is held in a specific position. Diagnosed: door switch interlock contacts worn. Replaced switch. Total: $120 + $260 switch + $60 labor = $440.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Pizza shop in Pasadena · Bakers Pride Cyclone, 11 years old</h3>
        <p>Loud noise from convection chamber. Diagnosed: fan motor bearings end-of-life. Replaced fan motor with OEM Bakers Pride part. Total: $120 + $480 motor + $80 supplies = $680. Customer set on annual maintenance to catch the next failure earlier.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 04 HONEST SCOPE -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">04 · Honest scope</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">What we service, what we don't.</h2>

    <p><strong>We service:</strong> Blodgett Mark V and ZEPHAIRE, Vulcan VC4 and VC6, Southbend Marathoner Gold, Garland Master Series, Bakers Pride Cyclone, plus comparable mid-tier convection ovens. Gas and electric. Single and double-stack configurations. Convection fan and motor service, drive belt replacement, igniter, thermostat, door gasket, door switch, heating element.</p>

    <p><strong>We don't do:</strong></p>
    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li>New convection oven installation (specialty installer trade with gas line work)</li>
      <li>Combi oven repair (steam plus convection, see <a href="/commercial/oven-repair/combi-oven-repair/">combi oven repair page</a>)</li>
      <li>Custom hood and vent modifications (HVAC trade)</li>
      <li>Conveyor pizza ovens (different specialty, see parent <a href="/commercial/oven-repair/">commercial oven repair pillar</a>)</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 05 PRICING -->
